Use Case 1: Report Incident
Actor: Employee / Incident Reporter
Precondition:
User is authenticated and has access to the system.
Main Flow:
User selects the option to report a new incident.
User enters incident details such as type, description, and time of occurrence.
System validates the entered information.
System generates a unique incident ID.
Incident is stored in the centralized incident repository.
Alternative Flow:
If the system is unavailable or required details are missing, incident submission fails and an error message is displayed.
Postcondition:
A valid cybersecurity incident is successfully reported and recorded in the system.

Use Case 2: Initiate Response Workflow
Actor: SOC Analyst
Precondition:
SOC analyst is authenticated and an incident is assigned.
Main Flow:
SOC analyst selects an assigned incident.
System displays incident details and severity level.
System presents the guided response workflow.
SOC analyst performs response actions and updates progress.
Incident status is updated to “In Progress.”
Alternative Flow:
If the incident is already resolved or closed, the system restricts workflow initiation.
Postcondition:
Incident response process is initiated and tracked by the system.

Use Case 3: Monitor Incident Performance
Actor: System Administrator / Security Manager
Precondition:
Administrator is authenticated.
Main Flow:
Administrator accesses the incident monitoring dashboard.
System displays real-time incident statistics and severity distribution.
Administrator reviews response timelines and performance metrics.
Alternative Flow:
If no incidents are available, the system displays default or empty dashboard values.
Postcondition:
Incident performance and system activity are successfully monitored.

